dc_title_s: Chart of part of the Bahama Islands showing the tracks ascribed to Columbus on his discovery of the New World
dc_description_s: Scale approximately 1,100,000.|Relief shown by hachures and spot heights. Depths shown by soundings.|Includes references and 5 insets.|compiled and drawn, under the direction of W.T. Bright, in charge of Drawing Division, U.S. Coast and Geodetic Survey Office ; by T.J. O'Sullivan, draughtsman.
